me we will get False is when both of them are False.remember this is the or logic table and not the AND or NOT logic table dont worry about them until you need them  you will not be using them here.okay now that we have done some review on the logic of OR now lets look at our board_contains_word functionand the helper functions board_contains_word will need to return True or Falseboard_contains_word_in_row() and board_contains_word_in_column() already return True or Falseeach helper function can be though of as an expressionand we can put them in the logic tableword_in_row(board word)    word_in_column(board word)      word_in_row() or word_in_column(board word) True                                                        True                                                          TrueTrue                                                        False                                                         TrueFalse                                                      True                                                           TrueFalse                                                       False                                                         False  so the table above it the result of board_contains_word_in_row(board word) or board_contains_word_in_column(board word)and we know that the above expression will return True or False based on the logic tablenow the board_contains_word() function needs to return True or Falseand we have an expression that will return True or Falseall you need to do is write a return statement that uses the expression above, Resolved,2
